A unit of South African construction firm Aveng said on Friday it would cut 120 jobs mostly due to projects coming to an end and rebuffed a union’s claim that more than 2 000 workers would be affected. The National Union of Mineworkers (Num) said on Thursday it had received a section 189 notice that 2 863 workers would be laid off by Aveng unit Grinaker-LTA. Read: Aveng subsidiary to retrench 2 863 workers – union